summary: The Battle of Agincourt was a big win for England in the Hundred Years' War against France. It happened on October 25, 1415, near Azincourt, France. Even though the French had more soldiers, the English, led by King Henry V, won a huge victory. This boosted England's confidence and made them powerful in the war for 14 years. The English used lots of longbows, with archers making up most of Henry's army. The battle is famous in England and was even written about by William Shakespeare.
title: Battle of Agincourt
